I made a few notable changes to your code.

**Websites**

 1. Move your test data outside of the component
 2. Use `this.state` instead of class properties
 3. `map` over the data array. **Note:** the `key` prop must be unique ([source](https://reactjs.org/docs/lists-and-keys.html#keys))
 4. Change your React import. I&#39;m not sure if the wildcard import was a bug, but I&#39;ve never seen it done like that.

**Dashboard**

 1. **Don&#39;t call `setState` in the constructor** ([source](https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#constructor))
 2. Don&#39;t store your component in a property variable
 3. I moved your `onClick` to the `&lt;Button&gt;` component because that makes more sense to me. But, you can move it back to the `img` if you prefer or need it there.
 4. Made your class methods arrow functions to bind `this`

One last thing I&#39;d suggest is that, instead of manually handling the page routing like you&#39;re doing, perhaps use [`React Router`](https://reacttraining.com/react-router/).

